data.name: label1.Text
data.value:
To run Python code, you can use several methods depending on your environment:
Save your Python code in a file with a .py extension, for example, script.py. Open your command line or terminal. Navigate to the directory where your script is located. Run the script by typing python script.py (or python3 script.py depending on your installation).

data.name: label7.Text
data.value: IDEs like PyCharm, Visual Studio Code, or Anaconda's Spyder provide an environment to write, run, and debug your code. Create a new Python file or open an existing one. Click the run button (usually a green triangle or play icon) to execute your script.
